      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While some minor sprains resolve with rest, a \"bunch\" of ibuprofen can be risky, so stick to the recommended dosage on the bottle. If you are certain it's a sprain, elevating it above your heart and keeping it iced is your best bet for the next few days. However, if the pain is truly debilitating, consider an urgent care center instead of a full clinic for a quick assessment.",
      "source": "target",
